SQLBaseModel
Interface implemented by SQLModels which have other instances that require to be deleted from the database when main instance is deleted from the database Use Case : If an ingredient is deleted from the database, we don't want a recipe using that ingredient to be corrupted.
SQLBuilder<T extends SQLBuilder<T,R>,R extends SQLModel<?>>
The builder class is used to generalize all SQLModel builders and force them to define the two methods SQLBuilder.makeObjectFromResultSet() and SQLBuilder.makeObjectFromBuilder()
SQLContainer
Interface implemented by SQLModels that (virtually) contains other SQLModels.

SQLSubModel

SQLValue
This annotation is used to mark some attributes as "need to be inserted/retrieved in/from the database" attributes.
